"{\n    \"language style\": \"The author employs a clear, accessible writing style that combines journalistic objectivity with engaging narrative elements. Scientific concepts are consistently explained in layman's terms, making complex nutritional and medical information digestible for general readers. The vocabulary is sophisticated yet approachable, with technical terms always accompanied by plain-language explanations.\",\n    \n    \"narrative techniques\": \"The articles follow a consistent structure: opening with an attention-grabbing hook, transitioning to expert citations, and building through logical progression of ideas. The author frequently uses the 'expert interview' technique, weaving quotes throughout to add authority and credibility. Personal anecdotes and real-world examples are employed to illustrate abstract concepts. The writing maintains a balanced mix of scientific evidence and human interest elements.\",\n    \n    \"innovation\": \"The author innovates within the health journalism genre by creating multi-layered narratives that connect individual health choices to broader societal and environmental impacts. Each article moves beyond simple dietary advice to explore cultural contexts and systemic implications. The writing style effectively bridges scientific research and practical application, while incorporating contemporary relevance through references to current issues like sustainability and pandemic adaptation.\"\n}"